at?', 186, 0), (329743, 'Allow me to remove my headphones to listen to your bullshit.', 39927, 0), (329744, 'Observation:Thanks to technological advances, avid readers seem to be replacing DTBAD (Dead Tree Book Acquisition Disorder) with an alphabet soup of more more modern-day hoarding behaviors: EBAD (E-Book Acquistion Disorder), EGAD (Electronic Gadget Acquisition Disorder), and ABAD (Audiobook Acquisition Disorder). Of course, there''s also MYBAD (Movie and YouTube Acquisition Disorder: the hoarding or obsessive viewing of digital films and videos, some based on books). If any of these syndromes describes you, take heart: there''s probably an app for that! - 8/9/2013', 54266, 0), (329745, 'There is nothing more stimulating to the senses than that of a female body freshly emerged from a steaming hot shower, bathed in oils and feminine scents... well nothing except maybe a freshly opened package of chocolate double-stuffed Oreos.', 5237, 0), (329746, 'First, let me finish. Then interrupt.', 25186, 0), (329747, 'The American dream is actually Cuban.', 28027, 0), (329748, 'Merry Christmas," said George. "Don''t go downstairs for a bit.""Why not?" said Ron."Mum''s crying again," said Fred heavily. "Percy sent back his Christmas jumper." [I guess that''s a sweater, though my jury is still out on it until I get a future confirmation.]"Without a not," added George. "Hasn''t asked how Dad is or visit him [in the hospital] or anything...""We tried to comfort her," said Fred, moving around the bed to look at Harry''s portrait. "Told her Percy''s nothing but a humongous pile of rat droppings--""--didn''t work," said George, helping himself to a Chocolate Frog. "So Lupin took over. Best let him cheer her up before we go down for breakfast, I reckon.', 28, 0), (329749, 'Kind of a bummer, getting your butt kicked by a dead guy.', 54267, 0), (329750, 'Observ', 54266, 0);
